{
    "analysis": "We ran the full workflow: global thresholds (P95) were computed from full series, metric anomalies inside Mar 9, 2021 13:00–13:30 (UTC+8) were detected, traces were checked for P95 breaches, and consecutive-anomaly runs (faults) were extracted for IG01 and Tomcat01–Tomcat04. The consecutive-runs detection (run_length >= 2) returned a single fault: IG01 / JVM-Memory_7778_JVM_Memory_NoHeapMemoryUsed with a continuous run covering the entire inspected window (run_start_timestamp=1615266000, run_end_timestamp=1615267800, run_length=31). No consecutive anomaly runs (length >= 2) were found for Tomcat01–Tomcat04 in the same window. Traces showed IG01 calls to Tomcat services and only occasional trace P95 breaches, but metric analysis shows IG01 had a persistent JVM memory-related fault throughout the incident window. According to the diagnosis rules (if only one component KPI has a single fault in the window, that fault is the root cause), IG01’s JVM memory anomaly is the root cause. The earliest anomaly timestamp for this fault is 1615266000 (which corresponds to 2021-03-09 13:00:00 UTC+8). The underlying reason is persistent high JVM memory usage (non-heap memory).",
